{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:galatians.6",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 6 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:1",
      "text": "Brethren, if a man is overtaken in any trespass, you who are spiritual should restore him in a spirit of gentleness. Look to yourself, lest you too be tempted.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:2",
      "text": "Bear one another's burdens, and so fulfil the law of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:3",
      "text": "For if any one thinks he is something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:4",
      "text": "But let each one test his own work, and then his reason to boast will be in himself alone and not in his neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:5",
      "text": "For each man will have to bear his own load.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:6",
      "text": "Let him who is taught the word share all good things with him who teaches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:7",
      "text": "Do not be deceived; God is not mocked, for whatever a man sows, that he will also reap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:8",
      "text": "For he who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap corruption; but he who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap eternal life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:9",
      "text": "And let us not grow weary in well-doing, for in due season we shall reap, if we do not lose heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:10",
      "text": "So then, as we have opportunity, let us do good to all men, and especially to those who are of the household of faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:11",
      "text": "See with what large letters I am writing to you with my own hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:12",
      "text": "It is those who want to make a good showing in the flesh that would compel you to be circumcised, and only in order that they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:13",
      "text": "For even those who receive circumcision do not themselves keep the law, but they desire to have you circumcised that they may glory in your flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:14",
      "text": "But far be it from me to glory except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:15",
      "text": "For neither circumcision counts for anything, nor uncircumcision, but a new creation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:16",
      "text": "Peace and mercy be upon all who walk by this rule, upon the Israel of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:17",
      "text": "Henceforth let no man trouble me; for I bear on my body the marks of Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:galatians.6.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 6:18",
      "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit, brethren. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
